main event: Several objects of light were observed on three separate occasions in the area southwest of Tokyo, Japan on January 30, 1958.
interesting points: The objects were observed by USAF pilots and consisted of groups of 5 objects as well as single objects.
The objects flashed yellow to yellow-orange and moved in various directions with no discernible patterns.
The flashes were initially stationary but then moved rapidly for some duration.
After investigation, it was determined that the sighting may have been related to missile firings in the area.
The report includes detailed descriptions of the two USAF pilot observers, including their ranks, experience, and education backgrounds.
result: Inconclusive, possibly related to missile activity
photographs: Yes, but not present in this report
